1
00:00:00,047 --> 00:00:02,447
Large language models, or LLMs,

2
00:00:02,687 --> 00:00:07,087
are advanced AI systems trained on vast amounts of text data to understand and

3
00:00:07,088 --> 00:00:11,967
generate human-like language. Popular examples

4
00:00:11,968 --> 00:00:15,527
of large language models include GPT-4 from OpenAI,

5
00:00:16,287 --> 00:00:18,907
Lama from Metta, and Claude from Anthropic.

6
00:00:19,627 --> 00:00:23,247
Each of these models has been trained on trillions of words from diverse sources.

7
00:00:24,547 --> 00:00:27,827
Large language models can perform a wide range of language tasks.

8
00:00:28,407 --> 00:00:30,467
They can write essays and creative content,

9
00:00:31,127 --> 00:00:34,447
answer complex questions, translate between languages,

10
00:00:34,827 --> 00:00:36,847
and even generate and debug code.

11
00:00:37,487 --> 00:00:40,407
For example, given a prompt to write a poem about AI,

12
00:00:40,887 --> 00:00:45,627
an LLM might generate creative verse that captures key themes about artificial intelligence.

13
00:00:46,787 --> 00:00:51,387
Large language models are are a specific type of AI system within the broader

14
00:00:51,388 --> 00:00:53,407
artificial intelligence ecosystem.

15
00:00:54,047 --> 00:00:57,087
They're a specialized application of natural language processing,

16
00:00:57,327 --> 00:01:01,947
which itself is a branch of AI alongside machine learning and computer vision.

17
00:01:03,047 --> 00:01:07,027
LLMs represent some of the most advanced NLP systems available today.

18
00:01:08,007 --> 00:01:12,247
At their core, large language models are pattern recognition systems.

19
00:01:12,707 --> 00:01:17,027
They predict what text should come next based on patterns they've seen before in

20
00:01:17,028 --> 00:01:19,867
their training data. For example, given the prompt,

21
00:01:20,087 --> 00:01:24,507
the sky is, an LLM might predict blue as the most likely next word,

22
00:01:24,807 --> 00:01:28,467
with other possibilities like cloudy or clear,

23
00:01:28,907 --> 00:01:32,467
being less probable based on patterns in the data it was trained on.

24
00:01:32,727 --> 00:01:37,307
This pattern recognition happens across billions of parameters in neural networks that

25
00:01:37,308 --> 00:01:39,347
have learned to understand language context.

26
00:01:40,047 --> 00:01:44,907
The training process for large language models begins with massive data collection.

27
00:01:44,908 --> 00:01:48,227
Data is gathered from diverse sources including books,

28
00:01:48,507 --> 00:01:50,667
websites, articles, code repositories,

29
00:01:50,987 --> 00:01:54,247
and online forums. These data sets are enormous in scale,

30
00:01:54,647 --> 00:01:58,107
often hundreds of gigabytes or even terabytes of text.

31
00:01:58,967 --> 00:02:00,987
Before this data can be used,

32
00:02:01,227 --> 00:02:03,767
it must go through a rigorous cleaning process.

33
00:02:04,267 --> 00:02:07,907
First, duplicates are removed and obvious errors are corrected.

34
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:11,327
Next, the data is formatted into a consistent structure.

35
00:02:11,328 --> 00:02:15,027
Finally, harmful or inappropriate content is filtered out.

36
00:02:15,727 --> 00:02:18,287
Once cleaned, the text is tokenized,

37
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:21,527
broken down into smaller pieces like words or subwords.

38
00:02:21,987 --> 00:02:25,807
For example, the word brown might be split into bro and un,

39
00:02:26,287 --> 00:02:29,647
allowing the model to recognize parts of words it hasn't seen before.

40
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:35,227
The quality and diversity of training data directly impacts what the model

41
00:02:35,228 --> 00:02:38,707
can learn and understand, including diverse topics,

42
00:02:39,127 --> 00:02:43,887
writing styles, languages and domains helps the model develop a broader understanding

43
00:02:43,888 --> 00:02:48,567
of human language and knowledge. This carefully prepared

44
00:02:48,568 --> 00:02:53,127
data forms the foundation on which language models build their understanding of

45
00:02:53,128 --> 00:02:55,227
patterns and relationships in language.

46
00:02:56,047 --> 00:03:00,567
Neural networks learn language patterns through a specialized architecture called a

47
00:03:00,568 --> 00:03:05,107
transformer. A transformer consists of several specialized layers

48
00:03:05,108 --> 00:03:10,707
that process language in different ways. During

49
00:03:10,708 --> 00:03:14,587
training, the model learns to predict missing or upcoming words in text.

50
00:03:15,327 --> 00:03:19,967
The model analyzes the input words and tries to determine what word should fill

51
00:03:19,968 --> 00:03:23,767
the blank. It calculates probabilities for each possible word.

52
00:03:24,127 --> 00:03:27,287
Here, Matt has the highest probability at .7.

53
00:03:27,288 --> 00:03:31,627
The model compares its prediction to the correct answer and calculates the error.

54
00:03:33,307 --> 00:03:37,607
Based on the error, the model adjusts the weights of connections between neurons.

55
00:03:38,127 --> 00:03:42,707
Connections that help make correct predictions are strengthened while others may be weakened.

56
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:48,487
This learning process repeats billions of times across an enormous data set

57
00:03:48,488 --> 00:03:50,787
of text examples. With each iteration,

58
00:03:51,387 --> 00:03:55,367
the model gradually improves its understanding of language patterns and relationships.

59
00:03:55,368 --> 00:04:00,107
After billions of iterations, the neural network has learned complex language patterns

60
00:04:00,108 --> 00:04:03,027
and can make sophisticated predictions about text.

61
00:04:05,947 --> 00:04:10,627
To summarize, large language models are AI systems trained on vast amounts

62
00:04:10,628 --> 00:04:14,167
of text data. Popular examples include GPT-4,

63
00:04:14,667 --> 00:04:17,207
Elama, and Claude. They can write content,

64
00:04:17,627 --> 00:04:19,647
answer questions, translate languages,

65
00:04:19,967 --> 00:04:24,287
and generate code. LLMs are part of the NLP branch within the AI ecosystem,

66
00:04:24,288 --> 00:04:29,027
and fundamentally they're sophisticated pattern recognition systems that predict what

67
00:04:29,028 --> 00:04:30,207
text should come next.